The most common bug to avoid when implementing the Fibonacci function is an infinite recursion caused by not properly handling the base cases, which can lead to a stack overflow error. 

```python
def fib(n):
    if n <= 0:
        return 0
    elif n == 1:
        return 1
    else:
        return fib(n-1) + fib(n-2)
```
